robomagellan ROS package

A diagram describing the ROS nodes:
https://cacoo.com/diagrams/XSM34UVvYIzbXs1b
A diagram describing the tf mappings:
https://cacoo.com/diagrams/kHPU6kID4jruOZMA

SETUP/PREREQUISITES

Install ROS Fuerte
  you have two options: install desktop-full, or install comm (bare bones) page and then install:
    ros-fuerte-navigation
    ros-fuerte-geometry
    ros-fuerte-robot-model
    ros-fuerte-rqt  (note: this is used for dynamic_reconfigure, and only needs
                     to be on the controlling machine, not the robot itself)
  setup dynamic_reconfigure
    rosdep install dynamic_reconfigure
    rosmake dynamic_reconfigure
Install opencv and opencv python bindings
Install python-pyproj (GPS nodes requires it)
  sudo apt-get install python-pyproj
make sure the current directory (robomagellan) is on your ROS_PACKAGE_PATH
chmod +x nodes/*.py

TO RUN (SIMULATION)

rosmake
# see robomagellan.launch for a set of possible WORLDNAME values
roslaunch robomagellan robomagellan.launch simulation:=true worldname:=WORLDNAME

TO RUN (PRODUCTION)

rosmake
roslaunch robomagellan robomagellan.launch


